# MR. FACE — App Structure & Home Screen

Quick reference for the homepage layout and terminology.

## Application name
- Header title is always **"MR. FACE"** (replaces previous "Choose character" / "Choose game" titles).

## Home screen layout (top → bottom)

1. **Customize Character** (one row, left to right)
   - **Character** dropdown: selects which character (head + face mesh + head topper) to use. Default: "Z baby". Each option is a saved character (from upload or test photo).
   - **Upload** button: single button (no photo icon) to upload a new face photo; adds or replaces character.
   - **Hue slider**: adjusts helmet (head topper) color.
   - In this app, **Character** = head (face mesh + back shell) + head topper (currently helmet).

2. **3D view**
   - Canvas showing the selected character; orbit/zoom.

3. **Game swiper**
   - Selects the **game** (body/kart/vehicle and mode). Options: **Waterpark** (default), **Kart**.
   - **Game** = body, kart, and game logic (e.g. Kart racing, Waterpark — to be defined elsewhere).

4. **PLAY** button
   - Starts the selected game with the selected character. Disabled when there are no characters.

## Screens & flow
- `home`: character customization + game selection + PLAY.
- `cartGame`: Kart racing (existing). Entered when PLAY with game "Kart".
- `waterparkGame`: placeholder "Coming soon". Entered when PLAY with game "Waterpark".
- Game list: `GAMES` in `App.tsx`. Default `selectedGameId` in context is `'waterpark'`.

## Key files
- `src/App.tsx`: main shell, home UI, screen routing, PLAY handler.
- `src/context/AppContext.tsx`: `characters`, `selectedCharacterIndex`, `helmetHue`, `selectedGameId`, etc.
- `src/screens/CartGameScreen.tsx`: Kart game.
- `src/screens/WaterparkGameScreen.tsx`: Waterpark placeholder.
